---
scope: src/render
description: Pure function that formats a PackageHealth record into a complete, human-readable terminal report string.
intent: >
  The render module is the final step in the pkg-pulse pipeline. It takes a
  fully-scored PackageHealth record and converts it into the terminal report a
  developer reads. The consumer is a human at a CLI who needs to understand at
  a glance whether a package is healthy, which categories drag the score, what
  warnings demand immediate attention, and which signals were unavailable and
  why. Success means the report is complete, consistently structured, and
  honest about uncertainty — nothing is hidden, nothing is fabricated, and
  partial coverage is surfaced with enough context for the user to act on it.
outcomes:
  desired:
    - Every available category appears in the report as a labelled bar chart row with its numeric score and detail strings, rendered in a stable canonical order.
    - "The header identifies the package by name and version and states the overall score alongside signal coverage as a percentage."
    - Warnings are present and severity-tagged when the health record contains them, and the warnings section is absent entirely when the warnings list is empty.
    - Unavailable signals are listed by name and reason in the footer when any signals are missing, and that section is absent when all signals are available.
    - A confidence advisory appears in the footer whenever signal coverage is below 100%, and is absent when coverage is complete.
  undesired:
    - A warnings section rendered with a heading but no items, or a warnings section omitted when items are present.
    - An unavailable signals section rendered when the list is empty, or omitted when it is non-empty.
    - A confidence advisory rendered when coverage is 100%, or suppressed when it is below 100%.
    - Category rows appearing in an arbitrary or inconsistent order across runs.
    - Sections joined without blank-line separation, producing a wall of text with no visual structure.
---

